reviews.text: Just had the most fantastic experience here!  Called this morning needing a catered lunch for 10 and the staff accommodated me with a smile. The food is "off the hook" good and presented so beautifully!  Thank you all for the incredible experience!!!
The Wal-Mart coffee (K-Cups) is gross and no Splenda. Food is edible but prices seem a bit high for the area. I don't think I will be back.
Always good service and amazing food! There’s always a different special and you can tell the food is cooked with care.
I eat here everyday for lunch and keep coming back because the food is so good!! Tots recommend!!

I'm going to tell you right now I will be making Two stops; almost, every morning. On top of that it was my first time ever ordering today. Sally literally answered the phone, cooked my food boxed it, delivered "it" to Me, and when I sat down finally to eat It. Just the chicken alone by it's self.... was amazing.

See you in the morning Sally!

I followed the reviews here and I must say, incredible service and food! The restaurant staff is courteous and the establishment is clean. I ate the beef shawarma and it was excellent! I will be returning for sure! Thank you Sally!

My friend, Jerry and I have been wanting to try Sally's Cafe at 3012 N. Main St. for a while, and when we saw construction was completed, we stopped there for lunch yesterday. Friday, May 13, 2022.

As we're heading in, we passed a mature lady coming out, and I asked how it was.  She replied, "Amazing!" with a big smile.  Very nice endorsement!

Sal greeted us and got us seated right away. The decor is standard, but pleasant and comfortable.  I was impressed at how busy they were at 2:30PM, well after the lunch crowd.

Sal got our drink orders. I asked how the iced tea is and he asserted it is excellent. I agree wholeheartedly, it is excellent. Very nice and fresh.

Our waitress, Tala was very pleasant and upbeat, with a good, helpful attitude. I've been dying for a good gyro in Roswell for a LONG time, so Jerry and I both got the gyro wrap with fries and Jerry additionally ordered an appetizer of stuffed grape leaves.

I didn't have the grape leaves, but Jerry advised they were good.  The star of the show was the gyro. It is a generous size, with plenty of lamb and tzatziki sauce, served fresh and hot!  I rate this gyro a perfect 5 out of 5 stars.  The fries have some thickness to them, and they too were fresh and hot.

I love Baklava, but my diet doesn't permit it. Jerry had some, however and said it was very tasty. It would have benefitted from heating about five seconds in the microwave to give it just a hint of warmth, but it was excellent overall and very tasty.

For my gyro, fries, and iced tea, I paid a very reasonable $11.38 plus tax. That's about the same cost as eating at a fast-food restaurant, but miles better!

In summary, this was an outstanding lunch experience and I highly recommend Sally's Cafe. I trust and hope they will enjoy continued success, as I intend to visit often. All good wishes.
